corresponding eigenvalues of the mutually commuting square matrices {m1, m2, \
...}. It returns a list of the form {values, vectors}. Each row of values \
gives the eigenvalues of {m1, m2, ...} for the corresponding eigenvector in \
vectors. ", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
